        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the letters to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_571.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Bowman</ref>, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6071.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">30 March [1868]</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6081.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">2 April [1868]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Bowman had been away during CD’s visit to London in March 1868 (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6071.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to William Bowman, 30 March [1868]</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Bowman refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_373.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Bell</ref>. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6071.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to William Bowman, 30 March [1868]</ref> and n. 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Scrofulous opthalmia: inflammation of the cornea and conjunctiva associated with tuberculosis (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2119.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Dorland’s medical dictionary</hi></ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 161–2 n. 16, CD quoted Bowman’s observation. See also <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6081.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to William Bowman, 2 April [1868]</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
